The Radix or Epocha of Alexander the Great (which the Arabians call Aera Philippi) began the 4390. year of the Julian Period, the 3626. of the Creation, Nov. 12. the 425. of Nabonnassar, and the 324. Current before Christ. This Epocha was used by Hipparchus Ptol. Theon. Alexandrinus, (in Canonibus 

